tronics, and working-class conditions under globalization. Drawing on the author's rich analysis of four multinational electronics firms-from their boardrooms to boarding houses-Satanic Mills or Silicon Islands? makes a unique contribution to the study of work, labor, and high-tech production.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Apr 2019) 0aElectronic industry workerszPhilippines. 0aHigh technology industrieszPhilippines. 0aIndustrial relationszPhilippines. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Labor & Industrial Relations.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCOR eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066750940uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/9781501728730423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781501728730.jpg  a978-3-11-066750-9  COR eBook-Package 2000-2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles